Title: CISB5123
Subtitle: Text Analytics
Introduction:We are going to learn how to perform web scraping.
Steps:
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span class="jgG6ef" style="font-family: 'Lato'; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Inspect</strong></span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Inspect the website that you want to scrape to understand the website structure</span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span class="jgG6ef" style="font-family: 'Lato'; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Crawl</strong></span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Navigate the target website and download the response from the website</span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span class="jgG6ef" style="font-family: 'Lato'; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Parse and Transform</strong></span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Parse the downloaded data into HTML parser and extract the required data</span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span class="jgG6ef" style="font-family: 'Lato'; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Store</strong></span></p>
- <p class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" dir="ltr" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Store the extracted data for further usage</span></p>
